About the Role

We are looking for a passionate and experienced Senior Associate to join our Global Employer Services (GES) team — part of one of the largest and most dynamic professional services firms.

This is a strategic leadership role where you will drive client engagements, build strong relationships with government authorities, and lead a talented team to deliver exceptional mobility advisory services to multinational clients across industries.

Key Accountabilities

• Assist Managers and above in performing GES engagements, including Personal Income Tax, Payroll services and other required engagements.
• Assist Managers and above in preparing proposals and business development materials, identifying potential service opportunities and approaching strategic accounts;
• Assist Managers and above in developing standardization processes to improve efficiency and ensure risk management;
• Work independently and collaborate well with team members to prepare accurate working papers and/or concise and well-written reports using appropriate business and technical knowledge on a timely basis;
• Instruct staffs below to conduct research, analyse issues and draft advice related to clients’ issues including Personal Income Tax, Payroll, Labour and Social insurance (if any) and ensure quality of work delivered to Managers;
• Proactively get involved in working with the government authorities at national and local level to ensure a smooth working process.
• Provide timely guidance and direct feedback and mentorship that contribute to the ongoing development of the staffs in the team;
• Provide frequent internal trainings/updates to team members; and
• Develop and maintain distinct relationships with peers at client organizations/ government authorities;

